Uncommon Power / 2 :e_slime: / The Slime Boss

messages.content: i once was given this as a floor 1 card with i think recklessness and some useless card
i decided to try out the goop power over the tackle power
turns out there are so many sources of goop that this was absolutely worth speculating on
it really deserves its 2 energy cost because it is really strong damage scaling; i'd even say perhaps the strongest damage scaling card in slime boss's kit
shoutout to its ability to double <d~rain of goop>'s power

embeds.description: __**Rain of Goop**__: Apply 3 **Goop:p_goop:** to a random enemy 4 (6) times.

messages.content: rain of goop gonna be nerfed soon 😔
good
This card feels difficult to evaluate for me, It really seems like it shouldn't be very strong in comparison to inflame.

Sure slime boss has plenty of cards that apply goop, and the whole lick package, but spreading slime still probably doesn't work with at least 1/3rd of your deck most of the time, and it costs 2 to put in play

I feel like slime boss just has a much easier time scaling with the summoning mechanic and potency. I would definitely take this more often if it upgraded to 1 cost, but It feels difficult to take as is
i dont think potency is that good
the 2 cost is probably the worst part about it, but you apply goop as slime boss way more often than you attack as ironclad, and that's saying something
theres like 2 or 3 sources of it
slimes most of the time r basically just for their secondary effects
also there is a goop slime
so that's already cross-synergy available
I will say that I haven't had a run that really pushed the lick package, and that could definitely be biasing my opinion
u havent experienced the real lick experience until u get dead branch
theres so many 0 cost exhausting slime boss cards

messages.content: Just checked my slime boss history, I've gotten jeremiah's banner several times, and one crazy run with strange spoon plus tons of splitting cards. Potency definitely can shine under those conditions, but is probably less good on average
slimes are held back by proccing only once per turn unless you have command cards, and even then it's most likely only the front one getting the benefit
they're good enough, though
I will definitely try spreading slime next time I see it, definitely can be much better than inflame if you have lots of lick cards and rain of goops.

bonkers card, this one power can deal so much damage over the course of a fight. Really the only problem it has is that its hard to take it in act one. This card also stacks really effectively, theres even a potion that has the same effect.
theres so many slime boss cards that apply goop in separate intervals but even without those its still effective
The best thing that can happen for a lick deck is definitely early toxic egg as every lick upgrades to have a draw one effect allowing you to easily play 10+ licks per turn
My first ever slimeboss run was a full on lick deck with toxic egg, I took every lick card I've seen
Tongue lash and waste not are amazing for that kind of deck
also <Just Desserts>
